Description: Necklace made of coral beads with gold-plated pendants, chains and decorative elements.
Condition: Fair. There are some gold elements missing and others incorrectly strung.
Acquisition notes: Af2003,08.1 to 4 were given to the Museum by Dr Claudine Dauphin in 1997. This item was recorded as having been acquired in Egypt in 1970, and then given to the donor by her mother in 1970 in Holland. This collection was given to the Museum in 1997.
